% The public `backwater` API specs reference option types from external
% dependencies (`ranch:opts/0`, `ranch_tcp:opts/0`, `ranch_ssl:opts/0`,
% `cowboy_http:opts/0`) and a handful of internal types whose defining modules
% are intentionally hidden (`-moduledoc false`: `backwater_request:endpoint/0`,
% `backwater_module_exposure:t/0`, `backwater_cowboy_handler:opts/2`,
% `backwater_response:t/1`). The escript ex_doc resolves neither (deps aren't in
% the doc build; hidden modules expose no chunks), and it only supports
% suppression at the granularity of the *referencing* module, so we silence the
% whole `backwater` module here. Trade-off: a genuinely broken reference newly
% introduced in backwater.erl would also go unwarned.
{skip_undefined_reference_warnings_on, [<<"backwater">>]}.
